@viragen/backend dev: 
@viragen/backend dev: ## Project Style Guide
@viragen/backend dev: **Tone:** professional, innovative, and empowering
@viragen/backend dev: **Color Palette:** #3b82f6, #8b5cf6, #ec4899, #ffffff, #000000
@viragen/backend dev: **Tempo:** medium-paced
@viragen/backend dev: **Camera Style:** smooth tracking shots, close-up detail shots of UI/terminal, abstract visuals representing AI processes
@viragen/backend dev: **Brand Voice:** authoritative, intelligent, and trustworthy, with an emphasis on innovation, privacy, and user empowerment
@viragen/backend dev: **Must Include:** Cyberstrike logo and brand identity, Visuals of command-line interface (CLI) or terminal environments, Abstract or stylized representations of AI and neural networks, Imagery related to cybersecurity, penetration testing, and data flow, References to 'open source' and GitHub integration, Emphasis on user control and privacy (e.g., 'BYOK')
@viragen/backend dev: **Must Avoid:** Childish or overly casual aesthetics, Outdated technology imagery or stereotypes, Generic stock photos unrelated to technology or security, Sensationalist or fear-mongering security imagery, Visuals that suggest complexity or difficulty of use
